{meta: title The Prettiest Flowers Will Be Blooming}
{meta: artist The Forbes Family}
{meta: composer Albert E. Brumley}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I know there is a land of beautiful [F]flowers
Where we will [C]meet again where life is [G7]o'er
Where we will [C]while away the endless [F]hours
On heaven's [C]bright [G7]eternal [C]shore
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Oh the prettiest [F]beds of flowers will be [C]blooming
By the prettiest streets our eyes shall ever [G7]behold
And the prettiest [C]songs with the angels we'll be [F]singing
On the beautiful [C]morning [G7]by the river of [C]life 
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
In heaven I know there'll be no weeping or [F]dying
No chilling [C]winds or tempest ever will [G7]blow
It is a [C]land of love and wondrous [F]beauty
Where fragrant [C]flowers [G7]ever [C]grow
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Oh the prettiest [F]robes and crowns that we [C]all shall wear
By the prettiest streets our eyes shall ever [G7]behold
And the prettiest [C]songs with the angels we'll be [F]singing
On that beautiful [C]morning [G7]by the river of [C]life
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]On that beautiful [C]morning [G7]by the river of [C]life
{end_of_verse}
